% user level concurrency of course, the kernel itself uses
% lots of concurrency mechanisms (often mimiced also in userland)
%claude:
The concurrency syscalls provide low-level primitives for
user-level synchronization. [[RENDEZVOUS]] is a
meeting-point mechanism, and [[SEMACQUIRE]]/[[SEMRELEASE]]
provide kernel-backed semaphores. These are the building
blocks on top of which the user-level thread library
([[libthread]]) is implemented.

<<[[sys.h]] concurrency syscalls>>=
#define RENDEZVOUS  32
#define SEMACQUIRE  33
#define SEMRELEASE  34
#define TSEMACQUIRE 35
@
%TSEMACQUIRE ? timed semacquire?

