%claude:
And that is the entire syscall interface. There is no
[[getpid]]---a process reads [[/dev/pid]] instead. There
is no [[ioctl]]---device control is done by writing
commands to a file. There is no [[select]]---[[libthread]]'s
[[alt()]] uses [[rendezvous]] instead. The file server
abstraction absorbs what would otherwise be dozens of
special-purpose syscalls.

