%ocaml: bad name, it's more pg2by

% page, 4096, so when give page address, don't need 12 low bits! PGSHIFT
<<constant [[PGSHIFT]](arm)>>=
#define PGSHIFT     12          /* log(BY2PG) */
@
%c: bitshifting everywhere :) instead of using x / BY2PG use x >> PGSHIFT
%x86: same

\subsection{Raspberry Pi Input/Output devices}

% processors (CPU/GPU) are not everything. Also bus, devices.
% For Raspberry Pi,
%  - SD card for storage
%  - USB for keyboard and mouse (and more, like wifi card, camera, etc)
%  - GPIO
%  - etc.
% Will see later those things and how to interact with those devices.
%claude:
The Raspberry Pi is more than just a CPU. The BCM2835 SoC
includes a GPU with framebuffer, a USB controller (for
keyboard and mouse), an SD card controller (for storage),
GPIO pins, timers, and an interrupt controller. The kernel
must initialize and manage all of these devices.

