%claude:
Once the ARM starts executing the kernel, the boot proceeds
in three phases: (1)~hardware detection, populating the
[[Conf]] structure with the amount of physical memory and
other parameters; (2)~initialization of the kernel environment
(memory allocators, process table, device drivers); and
(3)~creation of the first user process, which runs
[[/boot/boot]]---the program responsible for mounting the
root file system, setting up the user environment, and
eventually launching [[init]] and then [[rc]] (the shell).
See Chapter~\ref{chap:initialization} for the full code.

