bank. The [[base]] is the start of usable physical RAM
(after the kernel binary and its static allocations),
and [[npage]] is the number of free pages. For example,
on a Pi~1 with 512~MiB of RAM:
\begin{verbatim}
  Physical memory:

  0x1FFF_FFFF +---------------------------+
              |                           |
              |  Confmem bank 0           |
              |  base = ~end              |
              |  npage = remaining pages  |
              |                           |
        ~end  +---------------------------+
              |  kernel text+data+bss     |
      0x8000  +---------------------------+
              |  firmware / Cpu struct     |
      0x0000  +---------------------------+
\end{verbatim}
%claude:
The exact values depend on the kernel binary size and
are computed at boot time by [[confinit()]].

%yoann: explain a bit kernel arguments and how passed by bootloader and what is kernelpercent (actually it will be more 20% I think than 60)
%claude:
The bootloader passes configuration parameters to the
kernel as key-value string pairs (similar to a Linux
kernel command line). These are stored in the [[confname]]
and [[confval]] parallel arrays. One important parameter
is [[*kernelpercent*]], which controls what fraction of
physical memory the kernel reserves for its own dynamic
allocations (via [<xalloc>]). The default in the code
is~60\%, but in practice a value around~20\% is more
typical---most memory should be available for user
processes.

<<globals confname and confvar>>=
// conf (boot) parameters *e.g. { "*kernelpercent*" => "60" }
// hash<string, string>
char *confname[MAXCONF];
char *confval[MAXCONF];
@
%ocaml: use hashtbl

<<constant [[MAXCONF]]>>=
#define MAXCONF         64
@ 
%old: used to be duplicated in every main.c, now factorized
\t but actually pb with bcm/ vs pc/ for getconf below

<<global [[nconf]]>>=
// Hashtbl.length(confname)
int nconf;
@ 

<<function [[getconf]]>>=
char* getconf(char *name)
{
        int i;
        for(i = 0; i < nconf; i++)
                if(cistrcmp(confname[i], name) == 0)
                        return confval[i];
        return nil;
}
