%claude:
Like [[cpu]], the [[up]] pointer (``user process'') is
per-processor: it points to the [[Proc]] currently running
on this CPU. On ARM it is stored in [[R9]]. The [[5c]]
compiler assigns [[extern register]] variables to registers
in decreasing order: the first declaration gets [[R10]]
(which is [[cpu]]), the second gets [[R9]] (which is [[up]]),
and a third would get [[R8]], and so on.
<<global [[up]](arm)>>=
extern register Proc* up;           /* R9 */
@


