\subsection{[[Cpu.ilockdepth]]}

%claude:
[[Cpu.ilockdepth]] counts how many [[ILock]]s are held
on this CPU. Like [[nlocks]], it is checked in [[qlock()]]:
sleeping while holding an [[ILock]] (with interrupts
disabled) would deadlock the entire CPU, because the
timer interrupt that drives the scheduler could not fire.
No atomic operation is needed here because interrupts are
already disabled when [[ilockdepth]] is modified.
<<[[Cpu]] other fields>>=
int ilockdepth;
@
% could rename nilocks?

% no need atomic increment/decrement below
% because used by only one cpu at a time! and no interrupt concurrency
% because interrupt disabled.

<<[[ilock()]] got the lock, update other fields>>=
cpu->ilockdepth++;
@
<<[[iunlock()]] decrement ilockdepth>>=
cpu->ilockdepth--;
@

<<[[qlock()]] sanity checks>>=
if(cpu->ilockdepth != 0)
    print("qlock: %#p: ilockdepth %d\n", getcallerpc(&q), cpu->ilockdepth);
@
