%linux: avoid redundant? use directly MMU to store this info?

%yoann: say this structure must remain small; you don't want 2KB of metadata about a 4KB page, wasting 1/3 of memory on bookkeeping data structures
%claude:
This structure must remain compact: there is one [[Page]]
per physical page in the system, so if [[Page]] were
2~KiB, a third of memory would be wasted on bookkeeping
for 4~KiB pages. In practice, [[Page]] is only a few
dozen bytes.

