%claude:
How much memory does all this bookkeeping consume? By
default, [<confinit()>] gives 80\% of physical pages to user
space and 20\% to the kernel. On a 512~MiB Raspberry Pi,
that is roughly 100~MiB for the kernel side: the [[Proc]]
array (about 6~MiB for 2000 processes at ~3~KiB each), 
the [[Page]] array (one [[Page]] struct per user page), the
[[mainmem]] pool (4~MiB), the [[imagmem]] pool (16~MiB for
graphics), etc. The remaining ~400~MiB is managed by
[[palloc]] as user pages.

