The [[Arch_KMap]] is needed to temporarily map the
physical page into the kernel's virtual address space
so [[memset()]] can zero it. On ARM with less than
2~GiB of RAM, all physical memory is accessible via
the [[KZERO]] offset, so this is trivial; on machines
with more memory, a temporary mapping is required.

