\subsection{[[Pagetable]]}

%yoann: introduce the data structure
%claude:
A [[Pagetable]] maps 1~MiB of virtual address space (256
pages of 4~KiB each). It is the second level of the
software page table---the [[Segment.map]] array is the first
level. The [[first]]/[[last]] pointers optimize iteration:
for a stack segment that uses only a few pages at the top
of a large range, they avoid scanning hundreds of nil
entries:
<<struct [[Pagetable]]>>=
