\subsection{[[newproc()]]}

%claude:
[[newproc()]] pops a [[Proc]] from the free list, assigns
it a fresh pid (by incrementing the global [[pidalloc]]
counter), and initializes its fields to safe defaults.
The new process starts in state [[Scheding]]---not
[[Ready]]---because its segments are not yet set up;
the caller ([<sysrfork()>] or [<kproc()>]) must finish
the initialization before calling [<ready()>].

<<[[Procstate]] cases>>=
