\subsection{Fork: [[RFPROC]]}

%claude:
When [[RFPROC]] is set, the kernel allocates a new
process, copies or shares the parent's resources
according to the other flags, sets up the child's
kernel stack so it will return~0 from the syscall (via
[<arch_forkchild()>]), and makes it runnable. The parent
returns the child's pid.
