\subsection{[[arch_execregs()]] (ARM)}

%yoann: last function call of sysexec, explain it and explain quickly Tos and say Tos later in Section X
%claude:
The final call in [[sysexec()]] is [[arch_execregs()]],
which sets the user registers ([[PC]] to the entry point,
[[SP]] to the new stack) so that when the kernel returns
to user mode, the new program starts. It also reserves
space at the top of the stack for the [[Tos]] (Time of
Stack) structure, which the kernel uses to pass timing
and profiling information to user space (described in
Chapter~\ref{chap:time}).

% sysexec -> <>
<<function [[arch_execregs]](arm)>>=
long
arch_execregs(user_addr entry, ulong ssize, ulong nargs)
{
    user_wp sp;
    Ureg *ureg;

    sp = (user_wp)(USTKTOP - ssize);
    *--sp = nargs;

    ureg = up->dbgreg;
    ureg->r13 = (ulong)sp;
    ureg->pc = entry;

    /*
     * return the address of kernel/user shared data
     * (e.g. clock stuff)
     */
    return USTKTOP-sizeof(Tos);
}
