\subsection{[[Waitmsg]] and [[Waitq]]}

%claude:
This is the data structure behind \plan's ``no zombies''
design. Instead of keeping the dead child's [[Proc]]
around (as \unix does with zombie processes), the child
writes a small [[Waitmsg]] (containing its pid, CPU
time, and exit string) to the parent's [[waitq]] and
then frees its [[Proc]] immediately. The parent collects
these messages at its leisure via [[await()]].
