%claude:
The Domain Access Control ([[DAC]]) and Access Permission
([[AP]]) bits together control who can access a page.
[[Client]] means the MMU checks the AP bits; [[Manager]]
means the domain bypasses all permission checks.
For AP: [[Krw]] = kernel read/write only,
[[Uro]] = user read-only, [[Urw]] = user read/write:

