%claude:
Now we see how \plan uses the ARM MMU hardware. Each CPU
has a single L1 page directory ([[cpu->mmul1]]), shared
between the kernel (upper half, mapped with [[Section]]
entries during boot and never changed) and the current
user process (lower half, populated on demand by
[[arch_putmmu()]] and cleared on context switch by
[[mmul1empty()]]).
%claude:
Each process keeps its own list of L2 page table pages
in [[Proc.mmul2]]. When the scheduler switches to a new
process, [[arch_mmuswitch()]] invalidates the old user
mappings from the L1 and the TLB; the new process's
pages are faulted in on demand.

