When the pager modifies a process's page tables (e.g.,
swapping out a page), it sets [[newtlb]] to signal
that the process must flush its TLB entries next time
it runs. [[arch_flushmmu()]] forces an immediate flush:

<<[[Proc]] memory fields>>=
