\subsection{[[schedinit()]]}

%claude:
[[schedinit()]] runs on the CPU's boot stack (set up
during initialization). It calls [[arch_setlabel()]] to
save the CPU's ``return here'' point in [[cpu->sched]],
then handles the outgoing process (putting it back on
the run queue if [[Running]], freeing it if [[Moribund]]),
and falls through to [[sched()]] with [[up == nil]].
When [[sched()]] later finds a new process, it calls
[[arch_gotolabel(\&cpu->sched)]] to return here.

