\section{Context switch}
% probably needs to see this section before sched() unless LP split
% sched() as I did.

%http://blog.tsunanet.net/2010/11/how-long-does-it-take-to-make-context.html

%claude:
A context switch saves one process's execution state and
restores another's. Unlike the full register save done
by [[_vsvc]] on a syscall (saving all 15 registers into
a [[Ureg]]), a kernel-to-kernel context switch only needs
to save [[SP]] and [[PC]]---because kernel code follows
the calling convention, and the compiler has already saved
any registers it needs.

\subsection{[[Label]]}

