\subsection{Kernel stacks}

%claude:
Each process has its own 8~KiB kernel stack ([[kstack]]),
allocated once when the [[Proc]] is first used and
reused across process lifetimes. This per-process stack
is where syscall handlers, page fault handlers, and
[[sched()]] run. It is separate from the CPU's boot
stack (inside the [[Cpu]] structure), which is used only
by [[schedinit()]].

