\subsection{[[arch_gotolabel()]] (ARM)}

%claude:
[[arch_setlabel()]] saves [[SP]] and [[PC]] into a
[[Label]] and returns~0. [[arch_gotolabel()]] restores
them and returns~1. This is the kernel's equivalent of
C's [[setjmp]]/[[longjmp]]---it is how the scheduler
switches between processes. The different return values
let the caller distinguish ``just saved'' from
``resumed after being switched out'':

<<function [[arch_gotolabel]](arm)>>=
TEXT arch_gotolabel(SB), 1, $-4
    MOVW    0(R0), R13      /* sp */
    MOVW    4(R0), R14      /* pc */
    MOVW    $1, R0
    RET
@
%ocaml: Thread.wakeup

% similar to C setjmp longjmp?

% schedinit | sched -> <>
