\section{Cooperative scheduling}

%claude:
In cooperative scheduling, a process voluntarily gives up
the CPU by calling [[sched()]], [[sleep()]], or [[yield()]].
This is the most common path: syscalls that block (waiting
for I/O, a lock, or a child process) call [[sleep()]] on
a [[Rendez]], which calls [[sched()]] internally.

