\subsection{[[wakeup()]]}

%claude:
[[wakeup()]] checks if anyone is sleeping on the
[[Rendez]]. If so, it clears the [[Rendez]] link, calls
[[ready()]] to put the process back on the run queue,
and returns the process. The woken process will resume
inside [[sleep()]] at the [[arch_setlabel]] return point:

<<function [[wakeup]]>>=
/*
 *  Expects that only one process can call wakeup for any given Rendez.
 *  We hold both locks to ensure that r->p and p->r remain consistent.
 *  Richard Miller has a better solution that doesn't require both to
 *  be held simultaneously, but I'm a paranoid - presotto.
 */
Proc*
proc_wakeup(Rendez *r)
{
    Proc *p;
    int s; // spl

    s = arch_splhi();
    lock(r);
    p = r->p;

    if(p != nil){
        lock(&p->rlock);
        <<[[wakeup()]] sanity check process state>>
        r->p = nil;
        p->r = nil;
        ready(p);
        unlock(&p->rlock);
    }
    unlock(r);
    arch_splx(s);
    return p;
}
@ 
