\section{Alarms}

%claude:
Alarms are a simpler, coarser mechanism than timers.
The [[alarm(ms)]] syscall arranges for a ``sys: alarm''
note to be posted to the calling process after [[ms]]
milliseconds. Unlike [[sleep()]], the process continues
running---the note arrives asynchronously, like a \unix\
[[SIGALRM]]. Alarms are stored as a sorted linked list
of [[Proc]] pointers, checked on every [[hzclock()]]
tick by [[checkalarms()]]:

<<struct [[Alarms]]>>=
struct Alarms
{
    // sorted_list<ref<Proc> (next = Proc.palarm, sort_key = Proc.alarm)
    Proc  *head;

    // Extra
    QLock;
};
@ 
