\section{Time of day}

%claude:
The time of day (wall clock) is maintained by the [[TOD]]
structure, which converts fastticks into nanoseconds since
the epoch using a fixed-point multiplier. The multiplier
is calibrated from [[cpu->cpuhz]] (the fasttick frequency).
A periodic callback ([[todfix]]) prevents the 64-bit
intermediate values from overflowing, and [[todset()]]
allows the time to be adjusted gradually (via a delta
applied over several ticks) to avoid jumps.

\t separate from Time? Less important for understand in first chapters

% see big comment at beginning of tod.c, in Kernel_extra.nw

%https://blog.packagecloud.io/eng/2017/03/08/system-calls-are-much-slower-on-ec2/

<<struct [[TOD]]>>=
struct TOD {
    bool init;       /* true if initialized */

    ulong   cnt;

    uvlong  multiplier; /* ns = off + (multiplier*ticks)>>31 */
    uvlong  divider;    /* ticks = (divider*(ns-off))>>31 */
    uvlong  umultiplier;/* Âµs = (Âµmultiplier*ticks)>>31 */
    uvlong  udivider;   /* ticks = (Âµdivider*Âµs)>>31 */

    vlong   hz;     /* frequency of fast clock */
    vlong   last;       /* last reading of fast clock */

    vlong   off;        /* offset from epoch to last */
    vlong   lasttime;   /* last return value from todget */
    vlong   delta;  /* add 'delta' each slow clock tick from sstart to send */

    ulong   sstart;     /* ... */
    ulong   send;       /* ... */

    // Extra
    Lock;
};
