\subsection{Exception vector initialization (ARM)}

%claude:
[[arch__trapinit()]] copies the [[vectors]] and [[vtable]]
code (from the Interrupts chapter) to [[HVECTORS]]
([[0xFFFF0000]]), disables all interrupts, and sets up
scratch stacks for each exception mode (IRQ, ABT, UND)
so that [[_vxxx]] handlers have somewhere to save
[[R0]]--[[R4]]:

<<struct [[Vpage0]](arm)>>=
/*
 *   Layout at virtual address KZERO (double mapped at HVECTORS).
 */
struct Vpage0 {
    void    (*vectors[Nvec])(void);
    u32int  vtable[Nvec];
};
@

<<constant [[Nvec]](arm)>>=
Nvec = 8,       /* # of vectors at start of lexception.s */
@

