\subsection{Virtual memory initialisation (ARM)}

%claude:
[[mmuinit1()]] finishes what [[mmuinit()]] started: it
records the L1 table in [[cpu->mmul1]] and removes the
identity mapping of physical address~0 that was needed
only while the MMU was being enabled:

% part 2

% main -> <>
<<function [[mmuinit1]](arm)>>=
void
mmuinit1(void *a)
{
    PTE *l1;

    l1 = (PTE*)a;
    cpu->mmul1 = l1;

    /*
     * undo identity map of first MB of ram
     */
