\section{Overview}

%claude:
This chapter covers the directory-related syscalls: [[create]], [[remove]],
[[chdir]], [[fd2path]], [[stat]]/[[fstat]], and [[wstat]]/[[fwstat]].
Directories in \plan\ are not fundamentally different from files ---
they are channels whose [[qid.type]] has the [[QTDIR]] bit set.
The kernel enforces a few directory-specific rules (no writing,
no exec, restricted seek), but most directory operations are
delegated to device drivers via the same [[\hlink{Dev}]] method table.
This chapter also presents the [[\hlink{Path}]] structure for tracking
human-readable pathnames, the [[\hlink{walk}]] function that resolves
path elements one by one through device drivers, and the
[[\hlink{DirEntry}]] structure (\plan's equivalent of \unix's [[struct stat]]).

% not that called often, but helps illustrate QTDIR introduced in chapter 3
<<function [[error_if_not_dir]]>>=
void
error_if_not_dir(Chan *c)
{
    if(c->qid.type & QTDIR)
        return;
    error(Enotdir);
}
@

