\section{[[sysfd2path()]] (a.k.a [[pwd()]])}

%claude:
[[fd2path]] returns the full pathname associated with an open file
descriptor. This is why the kernel must track [[\hlink{Path}]] objects
on every channel --- without them, there would be no way to answer
``what file is fd 3 pointing to?''. The implementation is trivial:
look up the fd, return [[c->path->s]].

