\section{Union mount}

%claude:
Union mounts allow multiple directories to appear merged at a single
mount point. When walking a name through a union directory, if the
first mount's device walk fails (the name is not found there),
[[\hlink{walk}]] tries the next mount in the list, and so on.
Reading a union directory is handled by [[\hlink{unionread}]], which
reads from each mount's channel in sequence, advancing to the next
when one is exhausted.

% seen already list of Mount in Mhead with next field in Mount and MBEFORE, MAFTER.

\subsection{Union walk}
<<[[walk()]] locals>>=
Mount *f;
@
% rename, bad name 'f'

<<[[walk()]] if c is a union mount, find and adjust type and dev>>=
/* try a union mount, if any */
if(mh && !sharppath){
    /*
     * mh->mount->to == c, so start at mh->mount->next
     */
    rlock(&mh->lock);
    f = mh->mount;
    for(f = (f? f->next: f); f; f = f->next)
        if((wq = ewalk(f->to, names+nhave, ntry)) != nil)
            break;
    runlock(&mh->lock);
    if(f != nil){
        type = f->to->type;
        dev = f->to->dev;
    }
}
@

