\section{[[sysmount()]]}

%claude:
While [[bind]] connects two local paths, [[mount]] connects a file
descriptor (typically a pipe to a file server) to a path, using the
mount device ([[devmnt]]) to speak 9P over the fd.

%ex of cmd? with spec?

<<syscall mount>>=
// int mount(int fd, int afd, char *old, int flag, char *aname);
long
sysmount(ulong* arg)
{
    return bindmount(true, arg[0], arg[1], nil, (char*)arg[2], arg[3], (char*)arg[4]);
}
@
