%claude:
The [[Kbscan]] structure tracks the current modifier key state for
the scan code state machine. When a Shift key-down event arrives,
[[kbscan->shift]] is set to true; when the key-up event arrives,
it is cleared. The next regular key press then consults these flags
to pick the right translation table ([[kbtab]], [[kbtabshift]],
[[kbtabctrl]], or [[kbtabaltgr]]).
The [[kbscans]] array has two entries: one for the built-in
keyboard ([[KbInt]]) and one for an external USB keyboard
([[KbExt]]), so each can track its modifier state independently.

