%claude:
Writing to [[/dev/cons]] calls [putstrn0], which dispatches to
whatever output backend is active: the [[screenputs]] hook for
display output, [[kmesg]] for the kernel message buffer, or
the serial port. The data is copied to a local buffer first
to avoid page faults while holding locks inside the output path.

<<[[conswrite()]] Qcons case>>=
case Qcons:
    /*
     * Can't page fault in putstrn, so copy the data locally.
     */
    l = n;
    while(l > 0){
        bp = l;
        if(bp > sizeof buf)
            bp = sizeof buf;
        memmove(buf, a, bp);
        putstrn0(buf, bp, 1);
        a += bp;
        l -= bp;
    }
    break;
@

