\subsection{[[/dev/consctl]] and raw input}

% who needs raw input? well rio, efuns!

%claude:
Raw mode is controlled by writing ``[[rawon]]'' or ``[[rawoff]]''
to [[/dev/consctl]]. When raw mode is active, [consread] bypasses
line editing entirely: each byte from [[kbdq]] is passed straight
through without waiting for a newline, and [echo] skips the screen
echo. The [[ctl]] reference count tracks how many processes have
[[/dev/consctl]] open; when the last one closes it, raw mode is
automatically turned off. This is important because programs like
[[rio]] that need raw keyboard input must not leave the console
in a broken state if they crash.

