%******************************************************************************
\chapter{Userspace System Programs}
%******************************************************************************
\label{chap:userspace}

% can execute them because they are in rootfs, via addrootfile,
% see mkrootall in mkfile via data2txt

%claude:
This short chapter covers the handful of programs that the kernel
needs to get from bare hardware to a running shell. These programs
are compiled into the kernel image itself (via the root filesystem)
so they are available before any external storage is mounted.
The most important mechanism here is the ``sharpbang'' ([[#!]])
support in [[sysexec()]], which is needed because the boot script
[[boot.rc]] is an [[rc]] script, and [[sysexec()]] must recognize
the [[#!]] header to invoke the interpreter.

\section{[[/boot/boot]]}

