%claude:
The cache operations are called throughout the kernel at points where
coherency between caches, memory, and the MMU must be maintained.
The most common pattern is after modifying page table entries:
[[cachedwbse]] writes back the modified PTEs so the MMU's page
table walker sees them. Before an MMU switch ([[arch_mmuswitch]]),
[[cacheuwbinv]] flushes everything because virtual addresses are
about to change meaning. The self-modifying FPU code calls
[[cachedwbse]] followed by [[cacheiinv]] to ensure the dynamically
constructed instructions reach the I-cache.

