\subsection{MMU}

%claude:
On the Pi~2, page table entries for DRAM include additional
attributes: write-allocate (so cache lines are allocated on writes,
not just reads) and sharable (so the cache coherency protocol
keeps the entry consistent across CPUs). These are critical for
SMP correctness---without the sharable bit, one CPU's cache could
hold stale data that another CPU has modified.

<<type [[PageTableEntryAttribute2]](arm)>>=
#define L1wralloc   (1<<12)         /* L1 TEX */
#define L1sharable  (1<<16)
#define L2wralloc   (1<<6)          /* L2 TEX (small pages) */
#define L2sharable  (1<<10)
@
%/* attributes for memory containing locks -- differs between armv6 and armv7 */
