\subsection{Local registers}

%claude:
The BCM2836 adds per-CPU ``local'' registers at physical address
0x40000000, above the main 1~GB RAM. These include per-CPU mailboxes
used to start secondary processors during boot: CPU~0 writes the
entry point address into a secondary CPU's [[startcpu]] mailbox,
and that CPU begins executing at that address. The mailboxes are
also used for inter-processor interrupts.

<<struct [[Mbox]](arm)>>=
/*
 * Arm local regs for SMP
 */
struct Mbox {
    u32int  doorbell;
    u32int  mbox1;
    u32int  mbox2;
    u32int  startcpu;
};
@
<<struct [[Mboxes]](arm)>>=
struct Mboxes {
    Mbox    set[4];
    Mbox    clr[4];
};
@



