%claude:
Each page carries a per-CPU [[cachectl]] array that tracks whether
the instruction cache needs to be invalidated when the page is
mapped. [[PG_TXTFLUSH]] is set by [[pio]] whenever a text segment
page is written (e.g., during [[sysexec]]). When [[arch_putmmu]]
maps this page, it checks [[cachectl]] and calls [[cacheiinv]]
if needed. The [[flushme]] flag on a [[Segment]] controls which
segments participate in this mechanism.

<<enum [[Cachectl]]>>=
enum Cachectl {
    PG_NOFLUSH	= 0,
    PG_TXTFLUSH	= 1,		/* flush dcache and invalidate icache */

    PG_NEWCOL	= 3,		/* page has been recolored */
};
@
<<[[Page]] other fields>>=
// array<enum<Cachectl>>
char cachectl[MAXCPUS];	/* Cache flushing control for putmmu */
@



<<[[newpage()]] other locals>>=
