\subsection{Extra segment types}

%claude:
Beyond the standard text/data/bss/stack segments,
Plan~9 supports [[SG_SHARED]] (memory shared between processes
via [syssegattach]) and [[SG_PHYSICAL]] (direct mapping of
physical memory, used for memory-mapped I/O like the VGA
framebuffer). Both are handled specially during [dupseg]:
they share the same [[Segment]] object rather than copying,
since the whole point is that multiple processes see the same
memory. For [[SG_PHYSICAL]], the page fault handler
([fixfault]) creates pages whose physical addresses map
directly to the device's physical memory, and marks them
uncached ([[PTEUNCACHED]]) so reads and writes go straight
to hardware.

<<[[Segtype]] other cases>>=
SG_SHARED = 04,
@


<<[[Segtype]] other cases>>=
SG_PHYSICAL = 05,
@
% SG_PHYSICAL used only for vga/vesa apparently


<<[[dupseg()]] switch segment type cases>>=
case SG_SHARED:
case SG_PHYSICAL:
    goto sameseg;

@

