%claude:
The qid encoding for [[/proc]] is cleverly packed: the low 5 bits
of the path identify which file within the process directory
(e.g., [[Qctl]], [[Qmem]], [[Qstatus]]), while the upper bits
encode the process slot number. The version field carries the pid,
so stale channels to dead-and-reallocated process slots can be
detected. The [[QID()]], [[SLOT()]], and [[PID()]] macros
extract these components.

<<devproc QXXX macros>>=
/*
 * Qids are, in path:
 *   5 bits of file type (qids above)
 *  26 bits of process slot number + 1
 *       in vers,
 *  32 bits of pid, for consistency checking
 * If notepg, c->pgrpid.path is pgrp slot, .vers is noteid.
 */
#define QSHIFT  5   /* location in qid of proc slot # */

#define QID(q)      ((((ulong)(q).path) & ((1<<QSHIFT)-1)) >> 0)
#define SLOT(q)     (((((ulong)(q).path) & ~(1UL<<31)) >> QSHIFT) - 1)
#define PID(q)      ((q).vers)
#define NOTEID(q)   ((q).vers)
@

