\section{Special keys and dumpers}

%claude:
Pressing F11 enables keyboard debug mode, which prints
every scan code as it arrives. F12 turns it off. Other
special key combinations dump internal state (memory
allocator, process table, etc.)\ to the console---invaluable
when the system is hung and you cannot type commands:

